      "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25wNE5ERllUbGRvTm5oMU5FNVFWR1ZvZEZwcU5YYxAB!2m1!1s0x89c259c83319f4d9:0xea4d618b5437c1d9"
    },
    {
      "name": "places/ChIJ2fQZM8hZwokR2cE3VIthTeo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s4M2RWUnhhVEpNUldOUExTMUtNV1ZwU1d4cGRGRRAB",
      "relativePublishTimeDescription": "10 months ago",
      "rating": 2,
      "text": {
        "text": "On Friday August 8th at 3:30 pm, I had a good experience at the salon.  The salon was nice and clean.  I got a regular manicure and pedicure.  I left the salon and my nails looked great!  I was very careful not to do anything that night because I didnt't want to chip my nails.  No cooking, cleaning dishes, etc..  After my shower that night, I got out of the shower and some of my nails were chipped.  Soooo disappointing since the next day was my wedding!  I was never so disappointed and upset. I wish I would have saved my $50 and went somewhere else.",
        "languageCode": "en"
      },
      "originalText": {
        "text": "On Friday August 8th at 3:30 pm, I had a good experience at the salon.  The salon was nice and clean.  I got a regular manicure and pedicure.  I left the salon and my nails looked great!  I was very careful not to do anything that night because I didnt't want to chip my nails.  No cooking, cleaning dishes, etc..  After my shower that night, I got out of the shower and some of my nails were chipped.  Soooo disappointing since the next day was my wedding!  I was never so disappointed and upset. I wish I would have saved my $50 and went somewhere else.",
        "languageCode": "en"
      },
      "authorAttribution": {
        "displayName": "Barb Fox",
        "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101278103027603217501/reviews",
        "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYcVjFOSuI2W1zRyI03-bDmWEfSi_3I0TvzWMUw6zuErBq7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2"
      },
      "publishTime": "2025-08-10T13:37:05.737254619Z",
      "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s4M2RWUnhhVEpNUldOUExTMUtNV1ZwU1d4cGRGRRAB&d=17924085&t=1",
      "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s4M2RWUnhhVEpNUldOUExTMUtNV1ZwU1d4cGRGRRAB!2m1!1s0x89c259c83319f4d9:0xea4d618b5437c1d9"
    },
    {
      "name": "places/ChIJ2fQZM8hZwokR2cE3VIthTeo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2paYWVFWTFja1k0WkhwSlgwVkpVbk5OV1dOc05IYxAB",
      "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago",
      "rating": 1,
      "text": {
        "text": "I arrived at the salon at 4:30 PM for a Gel-X fill appointment. Upon check-in, they confirmed the service and seated me right away. However, the technician (lily) completely removed all existing product from my nails and then performed three rounds of acetone treatment with cotton balls—even though my natural nails were already fully exposed and clean.\n\nAfter sitting for an hour and a half with no progress on the actual Gel-X application, I was switched into another techs chair. At this point I was running out of time and suggested we switch to regular gel polish instead. The technician (coco) insisted she could still complete the Gel-X tips quickly. However, what she actually did was apply full-coverage tips over my entire natural nails, and then painted my nails over with regular gel polish, which is not Gel-X at all.\n\nI was charged $160 for a service that was completely different from what was confirmed and promised. Not only did I not receive the Gel-X fill I came in for, but I was misled about what was being done and overcharged for an entirely different service. I have been getting tips on my nails for 12 years and this was one of the worst experiences I have had by far. Please do not go here.",
        "languageCode": "en"
      },
      "originalText": {
        "text": "I arrived at the salon at 4:30 PM for a Gel-X fill appointment. Upon check-in, they confirmed the service and seated me right away. However, the technician (lily) completely removed all existing product from my nails and then performed three rounds of acetone treatment with cotton balls—even though my natural nails were already fully exposed and clean.\n\nAfter sitting for an hour and a half with no progress on the actual Gel-X application, I was switched into another techs chair. At this point I was running out of time and suggested we switch to regular gel polish instead. The technician (coco) insisted she could still complete the Gel-X tips quickly. However, what she actually did was apply full-coverage tips over my entire natural nails, and then painted my nails over with regular gel polish, which is not Gel-X at all.\n\nI was charged $160 for a service that was completely different from what was confirmed and promised. Not only did I not receive the Gel-X fill I came in for, but I was misled about what was being done and overcharged for an entirely different service. I have been getting tips on my nails for 12 years and this was one of the worst experiences I have had by far. Please do not go here.",
        "languageCode": "en"
      },
